15 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 9], the following definitions
16 apply:
17 (1) “Domestic”, with respect to an entity, means governed as to its internal affairs by the law of this
18 state.
19 (2) “Domesticated entity” means the domesticating entity as it continues in existence after a
20 domestication.
21 (3) "Domesticating entity” means the domestic entity that approves a plan of domestication
22 pursuant to [section 3] or the foreign entity that approves a domestication pursuant to the law of its jurisdiction
23 of formation.
24 (4) “Domestication” means a transaction authorized by [section 2].
25 (5) "Entity" means a limited liability company, professional limited liability company, general
26 partnership, limited liability partnership, professional limited liability partnership, limited partnership, limited
27 liability limited partnership, benefit corporation, or nonprofit corporation.
28 (6) “Filing entity” means an entity whose formation requires the filing of a public organic record.
