16 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Nonexclusivity. A transaction under [sections 1 through 9] that
17 produces a certain result may not preclude the same result from being accomplished in any other manner
18 permitted by law other than in [sections 1 through 9].
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Reference to external facts. A plan of domestication may refer to facts
21 ascertainable outside the plan if the manner in which the facts will operate upon the plan is specified in the
22 plan. The facts may include the occurrence of an event or a determination or action by a person, whether or not
23 the event, determination, or action is within the control of a party to the transaction.
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 10. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 6 9] are intended to be
26 codified as a new part in Title 35, chapter 8, and the provisions of Title 35, chapter 8, apply to [sections 1
27 through 6 9].
